Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.03,0:00:05.62,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,In Vienna, two maternity\Nwards sat under
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.62,0:00:07.00,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,one hospital roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.00,0:00:08.38,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The First Clinic was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.38,0:00:09.70,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,run by doctors and\Nstudents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.60,0:00:12.14,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The Second was run by\Nmidwives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.93,0:00:14.09,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The patients were similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.87,0:00:16.11,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The death rates were not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.07,0:00:20.18,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,By 1846, the First Clinic\Nwas losing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.18,0:00:22.44,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,more than one in ten\Nmothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.44,0:00:25.44,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Across the same years, the\NSecond stayed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:26.62,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,under four percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.62,0:00:27.81,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Semmelweis found the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.81,0:00:28.99,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,difference in the routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.05,0:00:32.44,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Doctors moved from\Nautopsies to childbirth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.44,0:00:34.19,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,without effective\Ndisinfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.19,0:00:35.95,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,He
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.95,0:00:37.66,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,required chloride-of-lime\Nhand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.66,0:00:39.14,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,disinfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.14,0:00:40.63,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Mortality fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.63,0:00:42.12,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.12,0:00:44.21,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,worked before germ theory\Ncould explain
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.21,0:00:45.49,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,why.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.49,0:00:46.77,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,That was the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.77,0:00:49.02,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Believing the data meant\Nbelieving doctors
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.02,0:00:50.92,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,had been carrying death\Nfrom the dead
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.92,0:00:52.08,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,to the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.08,0:00:53.24,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The institution protected
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.24,0:00:55.69,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,its identity longer than\Nit protected the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.69,0:00:57.38,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.38,0:00:59.07,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Small causes, massive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.07,0:01:00.39,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,consequences.
